We use a dynamic programming approach to solve the problem. We create a 2D array (dp) with dimensions (n+1)x(m+1), where n is the length of string s and m is the length of string t. We iterate through the strings s and t to fill the dp array. If the characters at positions i-1 in s and j-1 in t are equal, we increment the value at position (i, j) in the dp array by 1. Otherwise, we take the maximum value between positions (i-1, j) and (i, j-1) in the dp array. Finally, we return the value at position (n, m), which represents the length of the longest palindrome that can be formed.

